Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a protocol to increase the source-destination secrecy rate, which is a key concept in information theory. The paper also derives achievable secrecy rates for the proposed protocol, which is a common topic in this sub-category.
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on improving physical layer security, which is a core topic in cryptography and security. The paper also proposes a jamming protocol to prevent eavesdropping, which is a common technique in this sub-category.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a relay protocol to improve the communication between the source and destination, which is a common topic in networking and internet architecture. The paper also formulates an optimization problem for power allocation, which is a common technique in this sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a joint relay and jamming protocol, which involves controlling the transmission and reception of signals. This is a common topic in systems and control, which deals with the analysis and design of complex systems.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of multi-carrier scenarios, which is a common technique in multimedia communication. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed protocol using simulation results, which is a common approach in this sub-category.
